        "scenario": "Partial failure during high load — connection pool exhaustion",
        "handling": "unhandled",
        "recommendation": "With synchronous calls to two downstream services (each up to 5s), CartService can hold connections for up to 10s per checkout. Under load, connection pool starvation is inevitable. Add bulkhead isolation (separate connection pools per downstream) and consider making the PaymentService call asynchronous."
      },
      {
        "scenario": "Payment gateway accepts charge but CartService already timed out — customer charged but sees failure",
        "handling": "unhandled",
        "recommendation": "This is the highest business-impact failure. Customer is charged, retries checkout, and gets double-charged. Requires idempotency keys on payment requests and a reconciliation job to detect and auto-refund orphaned payments."
      }
