      "reason": "CartService 5s timeout is shorter than OrderService worst-case (6s with retry) and PaymentService gateway timeout (8s). This guarantees orphaned orders and orphaned payments under degraded conditions. The blast radius includes double-charging customers and leaking inventory — both require architectural changes (saga/compensation, timeout realignment, idempotency) that go beyond configuration tweaks.",
      "routed_to": "MJ"
    },
    {
      "type": "integration_risk",
      "issue": "No compensation/saga pattern for partial checkout failure",
      "reason": "Sequential synchronous calls to OrderService then PaymentService with no rollback on payment failure means every payment failure leaks a stock reservation. At scale this will drain inventory availability. Need MJ to design the compensation flow (sync rollback vs async saga vs choreography).",
      "routed_to": "MJ"
